Job Description:

Torch Technologies is seeking an experienced Software Engineer to support ongoing Artificial Intelligence developments within several US Army programs. Tasks central to the position include: data mining; database design, integration, and interfacing; GUI development; and AI/ML implementation.



Job Requirements:

The qualifying candidate will possess the following:

Bachelor's degree (or higher) in Software/Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or Mathematics;



A minimum of eight years of software programming experience;



Strong knowledge of Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning capabilities, tactics, and implementation;



Database skills including data and object modeling and relational applications;



Data interface and GUI development experience;



Active DOD SECRET security clearance (inability to obtain SECRET security clearance will rule candidate ineligible).



Proficient interpersonal and written communication skills.



Additional desired skills include:

Work history with DOD programs;



Strong knowledge of radar and/or Position, Navigation, and Timing (PNT) systems.
